cutoff_energy_stats = generate_statistics(mean=8.64, variance=156, percentiles=(4.0, 4.4, 6.2), min_val=3.3, max_val=95)

    'Target Thickness-Energy': {'Pearson Correlation': 0.25, 'Spearman Correlation': 0.391, 'Covariance': 4.98e1},
    # ... include other pairwise statistics as needed for each feature combination ...
}

    """Generates a single data point based on feature stats and correlation with other features."""

                         sample['pulse_width'], sample['energy'], sample['spot_size'], 
                         sample['intensity'], sample['power'], sample['cutoff_energy'] for i, sample in enumerate(samples) if not np.isnan(sample['target_thickness'])])]

# Filtering out samples with invalid (NaN) thickness values as per the minimum and maximum bounds defined
